This question uses a sparse array representation. A sparse array stores only nonzero values, along with each value's row and column indexes.

```java
public class SparseArrayEntry
{
  private int row;
  private int col;
  private int value;

  public SparseArrayEntry(int r, int c, int v)
  {
    row = r;
    col = c;
    value = v;
  }

  public int getRow() { return row; }
  public int getCol() { return col; }
  public int getValue() { return value; }
}

public class SparseArray
{
  private int numRows;
  private int numCols;
  private List<SparseArrayEntry> entries;

  public SparseArray()
  {
    entries = new ArrayList<SparseArrayEntry>();
  }

  public int getNumRows() { return numRows; }
  public int getNumCols() { return numCols; }

  public int getValueAt(int row, int col)
  {
    /* to be implemented in part (a) */
  }

  public void removeColumn(int col)
  {
    /* to be implemented in part (b) */
  }
}
```

In the sample array, `numRows` is `6`, `numCols` is `5`, and the nonzero entries are `(row 1, col 4, value 4)`, `(row 2, col 0, value 1)`, `(row 3, col 1, value -9)`, and `(row 1, col 1, value 5)`.

Part (a): Write method `getValueAt`. The method returns the value at the given row and column. If no entry in `entries` has the specified row and column, the method returns `0`.

Part (b): Write method `removeColumn`. After removing the specified column, entries in that column are removed, entries in columns to the right are replaced by entries whose column index is one less, and `numCols` is decremented.

rubric.reference_solution:
One acceptable implementation is:

```java
public int getValueAt(int row, int col)
{
  for (SparseArrayEntry entry : entries)
  {
    if (entry.getRow() == row && entry.getCol() == col)
    {
      return entry.getValue();
    }
  }
  return 0;
}

public void removeColumn(int col)
{
  for (int k = entries.size() - 1; k >= 0; k--)
  {
    SparseArrayEntry entry = entries.get(k);
    if (entry.getCol() == col)
    {
      entries.remove(k);
    }
    else if (entry.getCol() > col)
    {
      entries.set(k, new SparseArrayEntry(entry.getRow(),
                                          entry.getCol() - 1,
                                          entry.getValue()));
    }
  }
  numCols--;
}
```

